posts.subject: js filter app
posts.body:
I made an app that automatically mutes users (which I have downloaded on my computer) based on the contents of their 'data.json'.
In this thread I will post links to ‘filters.json’, which my app generated based on your suggestions and the content that I have downloaded.
In order to apply a filter, turn off the zeronet, merge the file (that I linked) with ‘filters.json’ inside zeronet’s ‘data’ folder, rebuild database, restart zeronet and update the site.

Mute 728 users that made a post 5000 characters long:
https://anonfile.com/uaebl635n1/spam_filter_json

Mute 171 users that made a post in all caps:
https://anonfile.com/E9e4l33ane/caps_filter_json

Edit: I have to warn you that the way I made this filter may also include posts that don't have any text. I do not recommend using it yet. If this post gets a (you), then I will fix it later.
